olive oil
1 packet penne
1 leek
1 packet beef & pork mince
1 sachet Aussie Spice Blend
½ bottle cream
1 sachet Chicken-Style Stock Powder
1 packet Chargrilled Capsicum Relish
1 bag baby spinach leaves
1 packet Grated Parmesan Cheese

• Boil the kettle. Half-fill a large saucepan with boiling water, then add a generous pinch of salt.
• Cook penne in the boiling water uncovered, over high heat, until ‘al dente’, 12 minutes.
• Reserve some of the pasta water (1/2 cup for 2 people / 1 cup for 4 people), drain and return penne to the saucepan.

• Meanwhile, thinly slice white and light green parts of leek.
• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over high heat. Cook leek and beef & pork mince, breaking up with a spoon, until just browned,
3-4 minutes.

• Add Aussie spice blend and cook until fragrant, 1 minute.
• Reduce heat to medium, then add cream (see ingredients), chicken-style stock powder and some reserved pasta water (¼ cup for 2 people / ½ cup
for 4 people), and cook, stirring, until slightly reduced, 1-2 minutes.
• Remove pan from heat, then add chargrilled capsicum relish, cooked penne and baby kale. Stir to combine.

• Divide beef and pork capsicum relish pasta between bowls.
• Sprinkle over grated Parmesan cheese to serve. Enjoy!

Little cooks: Add the finishing touch by sprinkling the cheese on top.